  "description": [
    "Sign Initiative No 4Workers Unemployment Insurance Bu WINLOCK WINS GRAFT PRIZEPage Four VOLUME 2 COMMUNISTS NOMINATE BRADLEY SENATOR Metal Trades Back AntiWar Congress e FRONT LINE 2 ALAN MAX Capitalisms Third Party The National Executive Com mittee of the Socialist Party at its recent meeting in Mil waukee rejected by a vote of 7 to 4 the proposals of the Communist Party for united front action In its statement the Nation al Executive Committee does not speak against the united front On the contrary it real izes the immense value to the labor movement of a un ited action of all elements against the danger of war and continued exploitation And with this bit of lipserv ice intended for the militant Socialist membership the NEC proceeds to stab the united front in the back The entire question accord ing to the NEC should be re ferred to the Second Interna tional and the NEC should take up the matter when it meets again in December In this way the NEC hopes to satisfy the membership that has been fighting for a united front making it appear that the NEC is taking the neces sary steps The Socialist leaders say that"
